PORTFOLIO

Laser Harp

A fun audio synthesis project using the PIC32MX. The harp frame was built by hand, and it uses visible spectrum lasers instead of strings. The sound is all generated real-time on the microcontroller. There was an article published about it on Hackaday, as well.

Embedded Emulator with Bluetooth Controllers

A project built using a Raspberry Pi. It involved some modifications to use a Super Nintendo emulator on the Pi. I also built custom Bluetooth controllers to play the games with.

Quadcopter Battery Management System

One of my projects during my summer 2019 internship at Moog.

Vehicle Control System

I can't talk very much about this project, but it was my summer 2018 internship working at a very early stage startup. I designed and updated the control systems for a self driving bicycle.

Cornell Rocketry

This was my engineering project team for my undergraduate career at Cornell. My responsibilities on the team varied over the years, from testing and validation (involving the centrifuge system pictured here) to radio communications and control.

16-bit Microprocessor VLSI Design

For a final project in a digital VLSI course, my group and I decided on the massive undertaking of designing a 16-bit microprocessor from the ground up. It used a simplified version of the Tiny rv2 ISA. My primary responsibilities were the register file and instruction decoder sub-blocks, as well as the top level integration.
